{"TopicId":135037,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"Part orientation issue","CreatedByName":"akron","CreatedById":116554,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-27T04:21:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"akron","CreatedById":116554,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-27T04:21:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHELP!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I have this problem with a couple of parts. Whenever I export these two from Unity, they show up backwards in the part selector, no matter what I do. I have tried rotating them 180 degrees in Unity, rotating them in Maya and exporting them to \u00A0Unity again. I have tried a new scene file in Unity with a newly configured partTools to no avail.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is what I see in the part selector and below is a picture of my Unity window. I hope someone can help!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/iEVe2wF.png\u0022 alt=\u0022iEVe2wF.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/3QktnyY.png\u0022 alt=\u00223QktnyY.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nli2work","CreatedById":106805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-27T04:35:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nzero out all pos/rot on sc_barom; then rotate sc_barometer so the front is facing Z- relative to sc_barom. whatever you attach PartTool script will be the part\u0027s reference root, it will always get zeroed out to match Unity World orientation during export.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nhere\u0027s some old visual reference I made; Unity root is all zeroed out, and the object at default orientation in VAB and SPH; as viewed from starting camera position\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00223eo1ww7.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/3eo1ww7.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nfront of your part pointing\u00A0Z- will face lower right corner in part list icon; X- will face lower left corner.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-27T04:39:09Z\u0022 title=\u002203/27/2016 04:39  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by nli2work\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"akron","CreatedById":116554,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-27T04:53:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222475361\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459053313\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022106805\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nli2work\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, nli2work said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nzero out all pos/rot on sc_barom; then rotate sc_barometer so the front is facing Z- relative to sc_barom. whatever you attach PartTool script will be the part\u0027s reference root, it will always get zeroed out to match Unity World orientation during export.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nhere\u0027s some old visual reference I made; Unity root is all zeroed out, and the object at default orientation in VAB and SPH; as viewed from starting camera position\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nfront of your part pointing\u00A0Z- will face lower right corner in part list icon; X- will face lower left corner.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOMG! Thanks for\u00A0your help! I was just\u00A0rotating the wrong thing\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;.;\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;.;\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022GdCfzSt.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/GdCfzSt.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGetting a node to orient properly through the CFG is still a challenge... I have yet to figure that one out\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-27T04:56:43Z\u0022 title=\u002203/27/2016 04:56  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by akron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T14:10:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222475378\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459054425\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022116554\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022akron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/27/2016 at 10:53 AM, akron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGetting a node to orient properly through the CFG is still a challenge... I have yet to figure that one out\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/115700-104-nodehelper-tool-used-to-edit-node-positions/\u0022\u003ECIT NodeHelper\u003C/a\u003E has the orientation marker. It will appear as a green line sticking out of the node during edit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"akron","CreatedById":116554,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T14:18:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222476971\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459174241\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Enceos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Enceos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/115700-104-nodehelper-tool-used-to-edit-node-positions/\u0022\u003ECIT NodeHelper\u003C/a\u003E has the orientation marker. It will appear as a green line sticking out of the node during edit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will give it a try. I hope it still works fine in 1.05 (and 1.1). Thank for sharing it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-28T14:19:04Z\u0022 title=\u002203/28/2016 02:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by akron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T14:24:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222476979\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459174727\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022116554\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022akron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, akron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will give it a try. I hope it still works fine in 1.05 (and 1.1). Thank for sharing it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does work. Still requires Blizzy\u0027s Toolbar to appear\u00A0and suffers from multiplying buttons in the stock applauncher. But that\u0027s not an issue for part development purposes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"akron","CreatedById":116554,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-28T14:25:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222476990\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135037\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221459175045\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Enceos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Enceos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does work. Still requires Blizzy\u0027s Toolbar to appear\u00A0and suffers from multiplying buttons in the stock applauncher. But that\u0027s not an issue for part development purposes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgreed. Good to know!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}